post_text: OWN It! students participated in a team building experience at the Mall of America yesterday in place of WE Day. They visited Sea Life and had a behind the scenes tour of the aquarium, had dinner, bowling and arcade games at Game Works and were able to shop and go to Nickelodeon Universe! It was a great experience!

post_text:
Ogilvie had a great Homecoming tonight! It started with our staff versus Kanabec County Sheriff‚Äôs Office volleyball game, which our staff dominated. Then we had our annual pep fest followed by tailgating and the football game. Pictured are our senior Homecoming court along with Deputy Justin Strom in the Ima costume, which was the result of the KCSO team losing the volleyball match. What a fun and exciting day!

A huge thank you needs to be extended to Sheriff Brian Smith for pulling the royalty and supporting OHS at various homecoming activities this week, Deputy Strom for being so involved within the school, and the rest of the KCSO/BADGES crew for assembling a volleyball team and always being willing to have fun with us!

post_text: What an amazing group of students and staff we have! OWN It! hosted a school wide hat day where students paid $1.00 to wear a hat for the day. In addition, proceeds from the coffee shop were also donated and in just 45 minutes, we raised $400 for a family in need! What a great way to extend our Month of Kindness to our community! A special thanks to the Kanabec County Sheriffs office for joining us this morning.
